        "timestamp": "2019-09-12 13:03:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nJust wondering, if derivedFrom now defaults to 0.0.0, will PDPs have problems doing a look-up of the type from which the type of interest is derived?  Wondering if derivedFrom should default to 1.0.0 instead of 0.0.0?  (Of course, if the derived-from version is something else, that won't work either.)\nMaybe the code is right to begin with (until they add derivedFromVersion), and we should handle it in the invoking code?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9b277b898d2dceee432dcd532ae3969ad2f62cd2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-12 13:09:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> Just wondering, if derivedFrom now defaults to 0.0.0, will PDPs have problems doing a look-up of the type from which the type of interest is derived?  Wondering if derivedFrom should default to 1.0.0 instead of 0.0.0?  (Of course, if the derived-from version is something else, that won't work either.)\n> Maybe the code is right to begin with (until they add derivedFromVersion), and we should handle it in the invoking code?\n\nAccording to TOSCA spec, they default to 0.0.0 - not 1.0.0. So I would stick with that for the moment.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
